# .cursorrules

This is the NicheVibe project - an AI-powered anime discovery platform.

CRITICAL REFERENCES:
- Read PRD.md for ALL product requirements, API specs, and database schema
- Read FOLDER_STRUCTURE.md for project organization
- Follow the Teal & Void color palette defined in PRD section 4.2

TECH STACK (from PRD):
- Next.js 14 App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS (custom void/teal/cold colors)
- Framer Motion for animations
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + pgvector)
- Google AI text-embedding-004 (768 dimensions)

COLOR PALETTE (NO purple/violet/indigo EVER):
- Background: #050508 (void-950), #0D0D12 (void-900), #13131A (void-800)
- Accent: #0CCEC0 (teal) - ONLY primary accent
- Text: #E8F4F8 (cold-100), #6B7E8A (cold-400)
- Success: #22C55E (green)
- Danger: #EF4444 (red)

DEVELOPMENT RULES:
1. ALWAYS check PRD.md before building any feature
2. API responses MUST match PRD section 7 (API Specifications)
3. Database schema MUST match PRD section 6 (Database Schema)
4. ALL colors MUST use void/teal/cold palette - NO purple/violet
5. Use config/discovery.ts for ALL tunable thresholds
6. Framer Motion for ALL animations
7. All API routes follow Next.js 14 App Router patterns
8. TypeScript strict mode enabled

BEFORE implementing any feature:
1. Reference the relevant PRD section
2. Check if there's a config file for the feature
3. Verify color palette compliance
4. Ensure database schema alignment

When I ask you to build something, ALWAYS:
- Reference the PRD section first
- Confirm you understand the spec
- Ask clarifying questions if the PRD is unclear
- Build according to PRD specifications exactly